Definition.WordDefinition: Chick \Chick\ (ch[i^]k), v. i. [OE. chykkyn, chyke, chicken.] To sprout, as seed in the ground; to vegetate. --Chalmers. [1913 Webster]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition:
Chick \Chick\, n. 1. A chicken. [1913 Webster]
2. A child or young person; -- a term of endearment. --Shak. [1913 Webster]
3. a young woman; -- often considered offensive. [slang] [PJC]
chick n 1: young bird especially of domestic fowl [syn: {biddy}] 2: informal terms for a (young) woman [syn: {dame}, {doll}, {wench}, {skirt}, {bird}]
